Privacy Policy
SteadyMic

Last updated: February 16, 2026

1. Data Controller

SteadyMic is developed and operated by Dzianis Milasheuski, an individual developer established in Lithuania.
Contact email: info@porconova.com

2. Overview

SteadyMic is designed with privacy as a core principle.
The App does not collect, store, transmit, share, or process any personal data.

No user accounts, registration, or sign-in are required.

3. No Data Collection

SteadyMic does not collect or process:

- Personal identification information
- Contact information
- Location data
- Device identifiers
- Usage analytics
- Crash reports
- Cookies or tracking data
- Advertising identifiers
- Any other personal data

The App operates entirely on the user’s device.

4. Local Processing

All functionality of SteadyMic is performed locally on the user’s device.
The App does not connect to external servers and does not transmit any information outside the device.

5. No Tracking

SteadyMic does not use tracking technologies and does not track users across apps, websites, or services.

6. Data Storage

The App does not operate external servers or databases.
Any settings or preferences are stored locally on the user’s device and are not accessible to the developer.

7. Data Sharing

SteadyMic does not sell, rent, disclose, or share any user data with third parties.

8. EU and U.S. Privacy Laws

SteadyMic is designed not to collect or process personal data.
As no personal data is processed, most obligations under the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable U.S. state privacy laws are not triggered.

If the App’s functionality changes in the future, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.

9. Children’s Privacy

SteadyMic is not directed to children under the age of 13.
The App does not knowingly collect personal data from children or any other users.

10. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated if the App’s functionality changes.
Any updates will be reflected by revising the “Last updated” date.


11. Governing Law

This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the Republic of Lithuania, without prejudice to mandatory consumer protection laws applicable in the user’s jurisdiction.

12. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
Dzianis Milasheuski
Email: info@porconova.com
